parts.text:
Hi — I’m the Cyoda Coordinator. How can I help you today? You can tell me if you want to:
- deploy or check an environment,
- set up or run locally,
- learn a concept or get an explanation,
- get design/guidelines,
- or build/create a feature or app.
i want to deploy my application

I’ve opened the environment selector in the UI — please choose an environment there.  
Once you pick one I’ll run check_environment_exists() and continue with deployment.

Note: Environments take 5–10 min to provision. Apps take 3–5 min to deploy.

parts.text: Develop an enterprise-grade payment processing system with multi-currency support, advanced fraud detection mechanisms, PCI DSS compliance, settlement management, transaction validation, and comprehensive audit trails

Thank you for the request. To get started, we need to set up the repository first. We follow a GitOps practice, which means the repo isn't just for code—it's the anchor for your entire project. Setting it up now ensures that every design choice and configuration we make next has a permanent home immediately.

I've popped up the repository strategy options for you to choose the language template and whether to create a new branch or use an existing one. Since we're building an enterprise payment processing platform with multi-currency support, fraud detection, PCI DSS compliance, settlements, validation, and audit trails, picking the right strategy now will let us initialize the appropriate Cyoda template and structure.

Please pick one of the options shown in the UI.

args.question: Which repository strategy would you like to use for this enterprise payment processing project? (This decides language template and whether we create a new branch or use an existing one.)

options.label: Python — Public repo — My Existing Branch
Python — Private repo — My Existing Branch
Java — Public repo — My Existing Branch
Java — Private repo — My Existing Branch

args.context: We're building an enterprise-grade payment processing system with multi-currency support, advanced fraud detection, PCI DSS compliance, settlement management, transaction validation, and audit trails. Choosing the repository strategy now enables the Cyoda templates to initialize correctly and keeps the repo as the single source of truth for the design and build phases.
